    {
      "type": "prose",
      "title": "Summary",
      "content": "Fixes a race condition in the token refresh flow where concurrent API calls could each trigger a refresh, producing duplicate tokens and invalidating the first. The fix introduces a **mutex lock** on the refresh endpoint — the first request acquires the lock, subsequent requests wait and receive the same refreshed token.\n\nAlso adds retry logic in the auth middleware: if a token is rejected during the brief refresh window, the middleware retries once after a 100ms delay before returning `401`. This eliminates the \"flash logout\" bug users reported under heavy load."
    },
